The spectroscopic pipeline 

The special dependencies of the code are: 
pylru, frozendict, dill

== Running on DESI data == 

To run on DESI data use the code  from the desi folder desi_fit.py
Run it without arguments to understand how to use it

== Creation of the template grid library ===

The first step is to read the template grid into the sqlite database

python read_grid.py --prefix /home/skoposov/science/phoenix.astro.physik.uni-goettingen.de/v2.0/HiResFITS/PHOENIX-ACES-AGSS-COND-2011/  --templdb ../templ_data/files.db

Then we create the interpolated spectra for different instrument setups
python make_interpol.py --setup test_setup --lambda0 4000 --lambda1 5000 --resol 5000 --step 0.5 --templdb ../templ_data/files.db --oprefix ../templ_data/ --templprefix /home/skoposov/science/phoenix.astro.physik.uni-goettingen.de/v2.0/HiResFITS/PHOENIX-ACES-AGSS-COND-2011/ --wavefile /home/skoposov/science/phoenix.astro.physik.uni-goettingen.de/v2.0/HiResFITS/WAVE_PHOENIX-ACES-AGSS-COND-2011.fits

Create the triangulation
python make_nd.py  --prefix ../templ_data/ --setup test_setup

Create the Fourier transformation of the templates
python make_ccf.py --setup test_setup --lambda0 4000 --lambda1 5000 --step 0.5 --prefix ../templ_data/ --vsinis 0,300 --every 50 --oprefix=../templ_data
